This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:

This session continued building `bat_viewer.py` (an interactive bat echolocation spectrogram viewer at `xpabat/bat_viewer.py`). The user's requests in chronological order:

1. **Smart decimation rendering** for zoomed-out views (merge calls per-pixel per-species)
2. **CLI arguments** for port and FLAC file
3. **Terminal progress feedback** during server startup/detection
4. **Performance + bounding box artifacts**: Fix remaining sluggishness and low-frequency noise in call bounding boxes
5. **Three new features**: (a) unique call IDs visible in UI, (b) per-species show/hide toggles, (c) species reference data + recording statistics panel
6. **Accordion redesign**: Replace species modal with an accordion-style right panel — call detail at top, species at bottom, content opens within the panel
7. **Exclusive accordion with internal scroll**: When one accordion item opens, others close; all headers always visible; content scrolls within its section (no panel-level scroll)

2. Key Technical Concepts:
- BatDetect2 neural-net detection (MPS GPU); 10,455 calls in 42 sequences cached in JSON
- Disk cache (`*.calls.json`) keyed by audio mtime + BD2_THRESH
- Spectrogram argmax contour extraction — root cause of low-frequency artifacts at call edges
- 20 kHz floor filter for `trim_call_contour()` — separates floor noise from real bat signal for western NA species
- Binary search on t0-sorted call array for O(log n + k) visible-call filtering
- Canvas batched rendering: one `beginPath` + many `rect()` + single `fill()`/`stroke()` per species
- Exclusive accordion with CSS `flex: 1 1 0` / `flex: 0 0 auto` toggling for panel layout
- Shared content pane (`#acc-sp-content`) for species accordion (one pane, swapped on click)
- `_setAccordionState(who)` JS state machine: null | 'call' | species-name
- `FREQ_LOW = 13_000` Hz (13 kHz), `FREQ_HIGH = 96_000` Hz; `A_NPERSEG = 2048`, `A_NOVERLAP = 1792`
- PROFILES dict with heuristic classification ranges + scholarly reference data per species
- `/api/profiles` Flask endpoint exposing scholarly data to frontend
- Flask backend + embedded HTML/JS frontend (all in one Python file)

3. Files and Code Sections:

**`xpabat/bat_viewer.py`** (~2050+ lines) — the main application. All changes this session were to this file.

**Smart decimation — new JS functions added (before `drawFreqAxis`):**
```javascript
// Binary search helper
function callsLowerBound(target) {
  let lo = 0, hi = S.calls.length;
  while (lo < hi) {
    const mid = (lo + hi) >> 1;
    if (S.calls[mid].t0 < target) lo = mid + 1;
    else hi = mid;
  }
  return lo;
}

function drawCallOverlays(specW, H, viewEnd) {
  const startIdx = Math.max(0, callsLowerBound(S.viewStart - 0.3));
  const visible  = [];
  for (let i = startIdx; i < S.calls.length; i++) {
    const c = S.calls[i];
    if (c.t0 >= viewEnd) break;
    if (c.t1 > S.viewStart && !S.hiddenSpecies.has(c.species)) visible.push(c);
  }
  if (!visible.length) return;
  const SPARSE_THRESHOLD = 400;
  if (visible.length <= SPARSE_THRESHOLD) {
    for (const c of visible) drawCall(c, specW, H);
    return;
  }
  drawCallsBatched(visible, specW, H);
  const sel = S.selectedCall;
  if (sel && sel.t0 < viewEnd && sel.t1 > S.viewStart) drawCall(sel, specW, H);
  const hov = S.hoveredCall;
  if (hov && hov !== sel && hov.t0 < viewEnd && hov.t1 > S.viewStart) drawCall(hov, specW, H);
}

function drawCallsBatched(visible, specW, H) {
  const dimming = S.selectedSeqId !== null;
  const bySpecies = {};
  for (const c of visible) {
    if (!bySpecies[c.species]) bySpecies[c.species] = { col: c.color, normal: [], dimmed: [] };
    if (dimming && c.seq_id !== S.selectedSeqId) bySpecies[c.species].dimmed.push(c);
    else bySpecies[c.species].normal.push(c);
  }
  const speciesList = Object.keys(bySpecies);
  const meanBW = {};
  for (const sp of speciesList) {
    const all = [...bySpecies[sp].normal, ...bySpecies[sp].dimmed];
    meanBW[sp] = all.reduce((s, c) => s + (c.Fmax - c.Fmin), 0) / all.length;
  }
  speciesList.sort((a, b) => meanBW[b] - meanBW[a]);  // widest first = behind

  function mergeRects(calls) {  // input already t0-sorted, no re-sort needed
    if (!calls.length) return [];
    const out = [];
    for (const c of calls) {
      const x0 = Math.floor(tToX(c.t0)), x1 = Math.ceil(tToX(c.t1));
      const y0 = Math.floor(fToY(c.Fmax)), y1 = Math.ceil(fToY(c.Fmin));
      if (out.length && x0 <= out[out.length - 1].x1) {
        const last = out[out.length - 1];
        last.x1 = Math.max(last.x1, x1);
        last.y0 = Math.min(last.y0, y0);
        last.y1 = Math.max(last.y1, y1);
      } else {
        out.push({ x0, x1, y0, y1 });
      }
    }
    return out;
  }
  if (S.showBoxes) {
    for (const sp of speciesList) {
      const { col, normal, dimmed } = bySpecies[sp];
      for (const [calls, isDimmed] of [[dimmed, true], [normal, false]]) {
        if (!calls.length) continue;
        const rects = mergeRects(calls);
        ctx.globalAlpha = isDimmed ? 0.05 : 0.18;
        ctx.fillStyle = col;
        ctx.beginPath();
        for (const r of rects) ctx.rect(r.x0, r.y0, r.x1 - r.x0, r.y1 - r.y0);
        ctx.fill();
        ctx.globalAlpha = isDimmed ? 0.10 : 0.65;
        ctx.strokeStyle = col;
        ctx.lineWidth = 0.9;
        ctx.beginPath();
        for (const r of rects) ctx.rect(r.x0, r.y0, r.x1 - r.x0, r.y1 - r.y0);
        ctx.stroke();
      }
    }
    ctx.globalAlpha = 1;
  }
}
```

**`trim_call_contour()` — Python function added before `try_load_cache()`:**
```python
def trim_call_contour(c):
    """Remove frequency-floor artifacts (< 20 kHz) from call contour and tighten Fmin/Fmax."""
    cnt = c.get("contour")
    if not cnt or len(cnt) < 2:
        return
    freqs = np.array([pt[1] for pt in cnt])
    mask    = freqs >= 20.0
    trimmed = [pt for pt, m in zip(cnt, mask) if m]
    if len(trimmed) == 0:
        return
    if len(trimmed) == 1:
        f = float(freqs[mask][0])
        c["contour"] = [[cnt[0][0], f], [cnt[-1][0], f]]
        c["Fmin"]    = round(f - 2.0, 2)
        c["Fmax"]    = round(f + 2.0, 2)
        return
    c["contour"] = trimmed
    tf = [pt[1] for pt in trimmed]
    new_lo = float(np.min(tf))
    new_hi = float(np.max(tf))
    if new_hi - new_lo < 1.0:
        pad    = (1.0 - (new_hi - new_lo)) / 2
        new_lo -= pad;  new_hi += pad
    c["Fmin"] = round(new_lo, 2)
    c["Fmax"] = round(new_hi, 2)
```

**Detection code fix — gating argmax to BD2's frequency range:**
```python
flo_hz  = max(FREQ_LOW  * 1000, p["low_freq"]  * 0.75)
fhi_hz  = min(FREQ_HIGH * 1000, p["high_freq"] * 1.25)
bm_seg  = (fb >= flo_hz) & (fb <= fhi_hz)
if not bm_seg.any():
    bm_seg = np.ones(len(fb), dtype=bool)
seg_f   = fb[bm_seg]
seg     = Sb[bm_seg, :][:, i0:i1]
prows    = np.argmax(seg, axis=0)
fc_hz    = seg_f[prows]
fc_t     = t[i0:i1] + chunk_offset_s
Fmax_k   = fc_hz.max() / 1000
Fmin_k   = fc_hz.min() / 1000
fpeak    = seg_f[seg.mean(axis=1).argmax()] / 1000
```

**`__main__` block with argparse:**
```python
if __name__ == "__main__":
    import argparse
    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(
        description="Bat echolocation spectrogram viewer",
        formatter_class=argparse.ArgumentDefaultsHelpFormatter,
    )
    parser.add_argument("file", nargs="?", default=AUDIO_FILE, help="Path to FLAC/WAV bat recording")
    parser.add_argument("--port", type=int, default=5001, help="HTTP port to listen on")
    parser.add_argument("--redetect", action="store_true", help="Ignore cached detections and re-run BatDetect2")
    args = parser.parse_args()
    AUDIO_FILE = args.file
    CACHE_FILE = os.path.splitext(AUDIO_FILE)[0] + ".calls.json"
    if args.redetect:
        print("--redetect: ignoring cache, re-running detection.")
    startup(redetect=args.redetect)
    print(f"\nStarting server → http://localhost:{args.port}  (Ctrl-C to stop)\n")
    app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=args.port, debug=False, threaded=True, use_reloader=False)
```

**PROFILES — expanded with scholarly data (7 species + Unclassified):**
Each profile now has: `name`, `short`, `Fchar` (tuple), `Fmin` (tuple), `dur` (tuple), `sweep` (tuple), `common`, `call_type`, `desc`, `habitat`, `range`, `ipi_ms`, `refs` (list of strings).
Species: EPFU (Eptesicus fuscus), LACI (Lasiurus cinereus), TABR (Tadarida brasiliensis), LABO (Lasiurus borealis/blossevillii), ANPA (Antrozous pallidus), MYLU (Myotis medium group), MYCA (Myotis small group).

**`/api/profiles` endpoint:**
```python
@app.route("/api/profiles")
def api_profiles():
    out = []
    for p in PROFILES:
        entry = dict(p)
        entry["Fchar"] = list(p["Fchar"])
        entry["Fmin"]  = list(p["Fmin"])
        entry["dur"]   = list(p["dur"])
        entry["sweep"] = list(p["sweep"])
        entry["color"] = COLORS.get(p["name"], "#888888")
        out.append(entry)
    out.append({"name": "Unclassified", "short": "????", ...})
    return jsonify(out)
```

