**New JS accordion state machine (just written, last edit):**
```javascript
let _openAcc = null;  // null | 'call' | species-name

function _setAccordionState(who) {
  _openAcc = who;
  const callWrap  = document.getElementById('acc-call-wrap');
  const spacer    = document.getElementById('acc-spacer');
  const spSection = document.getElementById('acc-species');
  const spContent = document.getElementById('acc-sp-content');
  callWrap.classList.remove('acc-open');
  spSection.classList.remove('acc-open');
  spacer.classList.remove('hidden');
  document.getElementById('acc-call-chev').textContent = '▸';
  document.querySelectorAll('.sp-acc-header').forEach(h => {
    h.classList.remove('acc-active');
    const a = h.querySelector('.sp-acc-arrow');
    if (a) a.textContent = '▴';
  });
  if (who === 'call') {
    callWrap.classList.add('acc-open');
    spacer.classList.add('hidden');
    document.getElementById('acc-call-chev').textContent = '▾';
  } else if (who) {
    spSection.classList.add('acc-open');
    spacer.classList.add('hidden');
    spContent.innerHTML = _buildSpContent(who);
    const hdr = document.querySelector(`.sp-acc-header[data-sp="${CSS.escape(who)}"]`);
    if (hdr) {
      hdr.classList.add('acc-active');
      const a = hdr.querySelector('.sp-acc-arrow');
      if (a) a.textContent = '▾';
    }
  }
}

function toggleCallAcc() {
  _setAccordionState(_openAcc === 'call' ? null : 'call');
}

function renderDetail(c) {
  // ... populates #acc-call-body ...
  // When call is selected: _setAccordionState('call') at end
}
```

**`buildLegend` — current state (NEEDS UPDATE for new DOM):**
The current `buildLegend` function still creates `.sp-acc-item` elements with both content and header, appending to `#acc-species`. This is **incompatible** with the new DOM structure (`#acc-sp-headers` / `#acc-sp-content`). This function needs to be rewritten to:
- Create only header divs with `data-sp` attribute
- Append to `#acc-sp-headers` 
- Click handler calls `_setAccordionState(sp)` (not `.classList.toggle('open')`)
- Checkbox stops propagation and toggles `S.hiddenSpecies`

4. Errors and fixes:
- **`trim_call_contour` ineffective for bimodal distributions**: First attempt used percentile trimming (5th/95th), which failed when the MAJORITY of contour points were floor noise (10 of 18 points at 15 kHz, only 8 at 67 kHz). Fixed by switching to a simple `freqs >= 20.0` floor filter.
- **Mode-cluster approach failed for genuine FM sweeps**: A cluster-based approach (find densest cluster within ±10 kHz, keep points within ±15 kHz) accidentally included noise points at 14.8 kHz when the bat genuinely swept from 44→26 kHz and the cluster center was at 29 kHz (14.4 kHz from noise = within 15 kHz radius). Fixed by simplifying to the 20 kHz floor filter.
- **`high.size < 2` condition prevented trimming single-anchor calls**: Changed to `high.size == 0` as the bail-out condition; single high-freq point handled as special case creating a minimal flat contour at ±2 kHz.
- **`detail-body` element no longer exists**: Old `renderDetail` referenced `document.getElementById('detail-body')` which was removed in the accordion refactor. Fixed by the complete rewrite to use `#acc-call-body`.
- **Old `buildLegend` referenced `#legend-list`**: Removed in refactor, replaced with `#acc-sp-headers`.
- **Edit tool mismatch on tooltip innerHTML**: The JS template literal had em-dash characters that didn't match exactly. Resolved by reading exact line numbers before editing.

5. Problem Solving:
- **Low-freq artifact root cause**: Not BatDetect2's detection boxes but our own `argmax` over the full 13–96 kHz band in time bins where the bat is silent. Two-pronged fix: gate argmax to BD2's frequency range during detection (prevents artifacts in fresh detections); apply `trim_call_contour` at cache-load time (fixes existing cached data).
- **Performance**: Binary search reduced visible-call finding from O(n=10455) to O(log n + k) per render frame. Removing the redundant sort in `mergeRects` eliminated O(k log k) per species group per frame.
- **Exclusive accordion with internal scroll**: Used CSS flex state toggling (`flex: 1 1 0` vs `flex: 0 0 auto`) rather than explicit height calculations. `#acc-spacer` holds the empty space between call section and species section when nothing is open; gets `hidden` class (flex: 0) when something is open.
- **Shared species content pane**: Instead of each species item containing its own content (which caused layout issues), a single `#acc-sp-content` div is shared and its content is replaced when a different species is expanded.

6. All user messages:
- "Try again" (session start, resuming from compaction)
- "It's still a bit slow when zoomed out. Also, I notice a lot of the calls tend to have some noise where there's maybe one or two data points at the beginning or end of the calls that are really low frequency, so it makes the detection box very large. Is this an artifact of BatDetect2, or does this have something to do with how you display its detection?"
- "Can you 1. Include a unique ID for each call. 2. Allow me to turn off and on different species (show/hide their call overlays) 3. For each identified species, show statistics about the data used for classification. If possible. e.g. scholarly data about frequency range and any other relevant statistics used for classification. So I can click on each species and pull up this data. And it will also then show statistics about the identified calls within this recording."
- "Instead of a modal dialog, have it so the species list works like an accordion widget. If I click on a species, it opens up inside the righthand pane. So the entire right hand pane is an accordion that by default has the current selected call expanded, and is pinned to the top, and then has all the species pinned down at the bottom, which can be expanded up by clicking on them"
- "When you expand one accordion option, the others should minimize. So when I click on a call, or click to expand the current call, it should minimize any open species. Also, the scrollbar should be within each accordion item, so that all the accordion options are always visible in the window, and the contents of the open accordion option scroll within it"

7. Pending Tasks:
- **Complete `buildLegend` rewrite** to match the new DOM structure (`#acc-sp-headers` only, no `.sp-acc-item` wrappers, `data-sp` attribute on header divs, click handler calls `_setAccordionState(sp)`). This is the critical missing piece — without it the species accordion headers won't appear.

8. Current Work:
Immediately before the summary request, the assistant was implementing the exclusive-accordion-with-internal-scroll behavior. The following changes had been completed:
1. CSS updated: new flex-based layout with `#acc-call-wrap.acc-open {flex: 1 1 0}`, `#acc-spacer.hidden {flex: 0 0 0}`, `#acc-species.acc-open {flex: 1 1 0}`, shared `#acc-sp-content` pane
2. HTML updated: `#acc-call-chev` default `▸` (closed), added `#acc-sp-content` and `#acc-sp-headers` inside `#acc-species`
3. JS `_setAccordionState(who)` function written and `toggleCallAcc()` + `renderDetail()` updated to use it

The **last Edit call** replaced the old `_callAccOpen`-based functions with the new `_setAccordionState` state machine. The `buildLegend` function has NOT yet been updated to match the new DOM structure.

9. Optional Next Step:
The immediate next step is to rewrite `buildLegend()` to match the new DOM. Currently it still creates `.sp-acc-item` divs (content + header) and appends to `#acc-species` directly, but the new structure requires headers-only appended to `#acc-sp-headers`, with content rendered on-demand into `#acc-sp-content` via `_setAccordionState`.

The user's last message was: "When you expand one accordion option, the others should minimize. So when I click on a call, or click to expand the current call, it should minimize any open species. Also, the scrollbar should be within each accordion item, so that all the accordion options are always visible in the window, and the contents of the open accordion option scroll within it"

The new `buildLegend` should:
```javascript
function buildLegend(colors) {
  const el = document.getElementById('acc-sp-headers');
  el.innerHTML = '';
  const counts = {};
  for (const c of S.calls) counts[c.species] = (counts[c.species] || 0) + 1;
  for (const [sp, col] of Object.entries(colors)) {
    const n      = counts[sp] || 0;
    const hidden = S.hiddenSpecies.has(sp);
    const hdr    = document.createElement('div');
    hdr.className = 'sp-acc-header' + (hidden ? ' hidden-sp' : '');
    hdr.dataset.sp = sp;
    hdr.innerHTML = `
      <input type="checkbox" class="sp-acc-chk" ${hidden ? '' : 'checked'}>
      <div class="sp-acc-swatch" style="background:${col}"></div>
      <span class="sp-acc-name">${sp}</span>
      ${n ? `<span class="sp-acc-count">${n}</span>` : ''}
      <span class="sp-acc-arrow">▴</span>
    `;
    const chk = hdr.querySelector('.sp-acc-chk');
    chk.addEventListener('change', e => {
      e.stopPropagation();
      if (S.hiddenSpecies.has(sp)) S.hiddenSpecies.delete(sp);
      else S.hiddenSpecies.add(sp);
      hdr.classList.toggle('hidden-sp', S.hiddenSpecies.has(sp));
      scheduleRender();
    });
    hdr.addEventListener('click', e => {
      if (e.target === chk) return;
      _setAccordionState(_openAcc === sp ? null : sp);
    });
    el.appendChild(hdr);
  }
}
```

